From a47c75032dca7c12005f2c0e6c0c39afa31e6e6c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 11 May 2026 21:55:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] airoha: an7563: enable LZMA decompression in U-Boot

The OpenWrt FIT image we ship for AN7563 carries a kernel
sub-image with `compression = "lzma"`, so booting via

    mtd read firmware ${loadaddr} 0x0 ${fitsize} && bootm ${loadaddr}

eventually drives bootm into image_decomp() with type
IH_COMP_LZMA=3. Without CONFIG_LZMA the LZMA branch is compiled
out and image_decomp() falls through to the default case, which
prints

    Unimplemented compression type 3

and aborts the boot.

Upstream defaults: CONFIG_GZIP is `default y`, but CONFIG_LZMA
is opt-in. CONFIG_CMD_LZMADEC selects LZMA, and is `default y`
only when CONFIG_CMD_BOOTI is on (AArch64). AN7563 runs in
AArch32 / ARMv7 and uses CONFIG_CMD_BOOTM, so neither path
pulls LZMA in by accident.

Enable it explicitly in the AN7563 EVB defconfig so the FIT
kernel can be decompressed by bootm.

Signed-off-by: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
---
 configs/an7563_evb_defconfig | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig b/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
index 750821d5..a47c7503 100644
--- a/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
+++ b/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
@@ -13,7 +13,8 @@ CONFIG_DEFAULT_DEVICE_TREE="an7563-evb"
 CONFIG_SYS_LOAD_ADDR=0x81800000
 CONFIG_BUILD_TARGET="u-boot.bin"
 CONFIG_FIT=y
 CONFIG_FIT_VERBOSE=y
+CONFIG_LZMA=y
 CONFIG_BOOTDELAY=3
 CONFIG_DEFAULT_FDT_FILE="an7563-evb"
 CONFIG_SYS_PBSIZE=1049
-- 
